CASE ANNOUNCEMENTS

October 1, 2008

[Cite as 10/01/2008 Case Announcements #2, 2008-0hio-5040.]

MISCELLANEOUS DISMISSALS

2008-1872. State ex rel. Doucher v. Brunner.

In Mandamus. This cause originated in this court on the filing of a complaint for a writ of mandamus. It appeal's from the records of the court that the relators have not filed a brief, due September 29, 2008, in compliance with the Rules of Practice of the Supreme Court and therefore have failed to prosecute this cause with the requisite diligence. Upon consideration thereof,

It is ordered by the court that this cause is dismissed sua sponte.
